@node "Requirements" "System Requirements"

   PPC hardware with a fast CPU of @{b}1GHZ@{ub} or @{b}highter@{ub} to plays videoformat of high compression
 level or with a big screen size. To fast CPU more big the video and the best to decompress
 the video codec as mp4, flv, mkv and DivX.

   -mpga.library for mp3 files (AmigaOS4.x-Amiga OS3.5-3.9).

  - The Hollywood pluggins:
        * OggTheora: ogg sound format.
        * OggVorbis: ogg video format.
        * AVCodec1-1: Videoformats.
        * MovieSetter: Movie Setter movies.
        * Scalable Vector Graphics: svgimage and xmlparser.
        * Apng: PNG animations.
    Availables:
        http://www.hollywood-mal.com
        http://www.aminet.net

    Others:
        * Graphic and sound datatypes.
        * WarpDTtypes. Special fast graphic datatypes. http://www.futaura.co.uk/
@endnode


@node "Install" "Installation"
   Copy V.A.M.P. where you want in your hard disk, USB stick, etc.
@endnode


@node "Play" "Playing"
   The window has the buttons to:
    - "Load"  multimedia file, it isn't a multimedia file a requester is opens to tell you.

    - "Play" multimedia file.

    - "Pause" multimedia file.

    - "Stop" the multimedia file.

    - "Speaker" Mute/Unmute the sound from movie, also clicking in the volume bar Unmute.

    - "Sound volume bar" to change the volume video or Unmute.

    - "Playing status multimedia file" the video position and rewind/forward.


    And with the mouse:
    - You can move the player in your desktop gettin the head's player window.

    - You can change the player size window getting from the right bottom.

    - With the mouse wheel you can forward/rewind the movie and as trick with Pause and the
      wheel you can go to video position that like you even to snapshot frames.

    - With the right you can hide/minize the player and paused the movie or moviex and song.
      This option under MorphOS and AmigaOS4.x only paused the movie.

    - With the third mouse button (under wheel) you can pause/unpause the movie or song.
      (This option not available under MorphOS).


    And the keyboard hotkeys:
    - A-a: About the program version, author.

    - C-c: Settings, here you can choose:
             * Codecs-Plugins: This is only for the  Windows version but  if you choose the
               Codecs,  V.A.M.P. doesn't play  movies because in  Amiga  there aren't video
               codecs as  under Windows.  If you  choosed  Codecs  please again  choose the
               Plugins because for the default V.A.M.P. uses them.
             * The drawer where save the snapshots.
             * Snapshot Format. You can choose save your  snapshot in the  standard formats
               graphic: bmp, png, lbm, jpg, the png format is by default.
             * JPG Quality: The jpg quality by default is 80% and more % biggest qualiy and
               Kbytes and less % also less quality and KB.
             * V.A.M.P. Skin: Here you can choose the skin, only you give to the player the
                        path with the drawer where are all buttons and skin.
                        If you  choose an empty  drawer  or one unit or  there aren't  some 
                        graphic V.A.M.P. use the default buttons and skin. 

    - ESC: Exit the program.

    - I-i: Information about the multimedia file.

    - S-s: Shot the V.A.M.P. player has showed, video, anin, gif, picture, and this snapshot
           is saved in png formatõby default these snapshot are saved in the V.A.M.P. drawer
           or where you load the multimedia file.
           To know that you shapshot a frame, sound the typical camera sound shot.
           Warning: This option under MorphOS doesn't work, but under AmigaOS4 and Windows 7
                    it works correctly.

    - L-l: Load file.

    - N-n: Reset the movie and it come back the begin.

    - SPACE: Pause/Unpause the video.

    Full screen mode:
          * Left Amiga key- A+Return: Playing the movie in full screen.


   The header messages, now the V.A.M.P. players shows messages, besides the time for the
   movies and music files.
   The status player as PAUSED and MUTE ON with music and video files.
   Showing pictures and its pixel resolution.
   With other formats as Amiga animations or gif show different status mesages. 
@endnode


@node "Limit" "Limitations"
   1. When you use V.A.M.P. and other player of video, sound or music, for limitations
      of programming  language it uses the  same sound channel that them,  crashed the
      VAMP program.

   2. When you play a video with V.A.M.P. and other videoplayer or viceversa the system
      freezes or crashes because the CPU doesn't work uncompressing two videos.

   3. Some video formats aren't supported, and other limitations of speed  with videos
      with a big size or a codec very compressed.

   4. Some pictures and videos with big screen sizes.

   5. With not multimedia files for example txt, the player crashed.

   6. With Amiga OS4.1 Update5 V.A.M.P. playing videos of some codec crash the system.

   7. With MorphOS and AmigaOS4 some options don't work.

   8. With Amiga OS4 playing movies and  songs has a low level volume,  the player has
      the level of Hollywood and it doesn't handle the AHI sound output but with Mixer
      tool you can raise the sound level.

   9. V.A.M.P. uses the Hollywood plugins in AmigaOS4 and MorphOS,  under Windows also 
      it cans use Video Codecs. NO configure in Amiga systems the use of video codes.   

@endnode


