@node "History" "Program History"
   @{b}0.93 B @{ub} (09.02.2013)
  - New compilation to use the new Hollywood plugin apng to play the png web animations.

   @{b}0.93 Chrysalis Special Pack@{ub} (31.01.2013)
  - Assigned iconify icon for V.A.M.P. in this mode.
  - Added Time clock to finish the video or song.
  - Corrected bug in the position bar.
  - New customize option for V.A.M.P. now you can use your own mouse pointer and it is
    very easy to make, a single PNG graphic with alpha channel.
    WARNING: The click zone is in the 0,0 cordinates of this pointer,  if you use some
    picture this zone can to be in the transparency air from it. 

   @{b}0.92@{ub} (18.01.2013)
  - Corrected the movie time clock, hours:minutes:seconds are showed.
  - Skinable, now you can make your own skin and buttons or choose other skin.
  - Corrected the handling and show the pictures,  the big pictures are scaled to this
    window.
  - Bugs correction.

   @{b}0.91@{ub} (24.12.2012)
  - Correction bugs in header messages.
  - Correction some bugs.
  - Remove the Full Mode with F1 key.

   @{b}0.90@{ub} (23.11.2012)
  - Graphic buttons, Graphic volume bar, graphic movie&song status pointer.
  - Skin in the button panel.
  - Text with the Percentage of volume on volume bar.
  - Correction of some bugs.
  - Compiled with the lastest Hollywood 5.2 version and as curiosity under AmigaOS 3.9.

   @{b}0.87@{ub} (07.11.2012)
  - Now when you try to load a movie and cancel  the loading if you are see other  movie
    the player continue playing the current movie.
  - In the header window the palyer show the movie name current playing.
  - With the third mouse  button (under wheel)  you can  pause/unpause the  movie except
    with MOS version.
  - Hide/minize  the  player with the right  mouse button if you  are  playing movies or
    moviex and  music in your  work place or in your house,  pausing and hide the player,
    this option also dosn't work in MorphOS and AmigaOS4 versions.

   @{b}0.86@{ub} (30.10.2012)
  - Corrected some bugs.
  - V.A.M.P. has a black background instead of gray-cyan background.
  - Corrected the playing little movies.
  - Two Full Screen Modes:
       * F1: Full Screen 1 playing the original video size.
       * Left Amiga key- A+Return: Full Screen 2  playing the video in full screen.

   @{b}0.85 Special Ultimate Version@{ub} (09.10.2012)
  - Deleted the window/full screen mode.
  - Corrected a bug with movie bar that paused the movie.
  - Add support to music and sound files, now V.A.M.P. plays these files.
  - The V.A.M.P.'s header shows the  player  status,  movie/sound time,  Pause, Mute On,
    showing pictures.
  - Windows version.
  - Support web: www.vamp.es and  yes only in spanish language,  although the player has
    the messages only in english.
  - Scaled the video and pictures with sizes more big than desktop screen to 75%.

   @{b}0.80 Special Ultimate Version@{ub} (03.10.2012)
  - Two full modes, Movie Window with black background and Full Movie in 800x600.
  - Autoplay when you load the movie.
  - The mouse wheel substitute to keys F and R to forward or rewind the video.
  - Correct the frame  showed when  you load a movie,  because  in some cases  the frame
    showed was a black frame.
  - Shortcut L-l to load the movies or pictures.
  - Add the option to save your snapshot  in the standard graphic formats and the option
    to choose the JPG Quality for this graphic format.
  - Windows version.

   @{b}0.70 @{ub} (26.9.2012)
  - Corrected the Mute work. Now Mute/Unmute the sound from the playing movie.
  - Corrected the Pause work.  Now when you press the  space bar the movie is  paused or
    played also when you touch the Pause button.
  - The option of Amiga Shadow or Classic  border has been deleted  because it is little 
    useful. 
  - Add the Movie time in the head window player.
  - New keyboard option available pressing the N-n the movie back to begin.

   @{b}0.60 @{ub} (12.9.2012)
  - Corrected the volume bar work.
  - Now VA.M.P. work to Full screen or Window mode.

   @{b}0.50 @{ub} (08.7.2012)
  - Snapshot the V.A.M.P. showed in the screen.
  - Settings to choose the drawer where saved the snapshots.
  - Added the Rewind/Forward step with 10 seconds.
  - The Information shows the video format.
  - Now you can choose between Amiga classic border or Ghost border for the window player.

   @{b}0.40 @{ub} (30.6.2012)
  - Drop files on the player available.
  - Fixed played gif files with little screen size.

  @{b}0.30 @{ub} (14.6.2012)
  - This Guide.
  - Fixed one bug in status bar.
  - Added mute button.
  - Added keyboard functions. Pause, Information and About.

 @{b}0.25 @{ub} (8.6.2012)
  - Fixed visual problems with big pictures biggest than the ScreenMode.
  - Added Information button.

 @{b}0.20 @{ub} (14.5.2012)
  - Added show pictures. 

 @{b}0.10 @{ub} (18.4.2012)
  - Initial release.
@endnode

